    <div class="contain">
        <div class="main-content">
            <div class="card">
                <h2>Historical Significance</h2>
                <p>
                    Pipili’s applique work traces its origins to the 12th century, linked to the rituals of the Jagannath
                    Temple in Puri. Artisans began crafting vibrant fabric overlays for temple decorations and chariot
                    canopies during Rath Yatra. This centuries-old craft reflects Odisha’s rich artistic legacy and devotion,
                    evolving into a celebrated tradition.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="card">
                <h2>Cultural Highlights</h2>
                <p>
                    The craft showcases Odisha’s flair for color and design. Artisans stitch intricate patterns onto fabric,
                    creating motifs of flowers, animals, and mythological figures. Used in lampshades, wall hangings, and
                    ceremonial items, applique work embodies the region’s creativity and cultural pride, passed down through
                    generations.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="card">
                <h2>Techniques and Materials</h2>
                <p>
                    Pipili applique involves layering bright fabrics like cotton or silk, stitched with precision onto a base
                    cloth. Artisans use contrasting threads and mirrors to enhance designs, often dyeing materials in vivid
                    hues of red, yellow, and green. The process blends skill and patience, resulting in stunning, durable art.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="card">
                <h2>Shopping Experience</h2>
                <p>
                    Pipili’s streets are lined with shops showcasing applique masterpieces—think colorful umbrellas, bags, and
                    bedspreads. Visitors can watch artisans at work and buy directly from them. Bargaining is common, and each
                    piece tells a story of Odisha’s craftsmanship, making it a unique souvenir or gift.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="card">
                <h2>Modern Relevance</h2>
                <p>
                    Today, Pipili applique blends tradition with innovation, appearing in fashion, home décor, and even
                    international markets. Designers incorporate it into sarees and cushions, keeping the craft alive. The
                    town remains a vibrant hub, drawing tourists and art lovers to witness this living heritage firsthand.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

